assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Musashi Seimitsu Industry Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells transportation equipment in Japan and internationally. The company's power train business provides differential, reduction, engines intake and exhaust, and transmission mechanism; and linkage and suspension business offer coupling, absorbing, and steering transmission mechanism. Its motorcycle business provides transmission assemblies, camshafts, and other parts which are used in motorcycles, general-purpose engines, ATVs, etc. The company was formerly known as Musashi Sangyo and changed its name to Musashi Seimitsu Industry Co., Ltd. in September 1963. Musashi Seimitsu Industry Co., Ltd. was founded in 1938 and is headquartered in Toyohashi, Japan.
